# Production-grade web search for LLM systems: A complete integration guide

Integrating web search into LLM systems reliably requires combining mature orchestration frameworks with AI-optimized search providers, implementing multi-layer security guardrails, and establishing robust failure handling. **The current landscape offers production-ready options across all layers**, with LangChain and Haystack leading frameworks, Tavily and Brave providing the best cost-to-quality ratios for search backends, and established patterns like ReAct and hybrid retrieval delivering proven results at scale. Systems like Perplexity (200M daily queries, 93% SimpleQA accuracy, 358ms p50 latency) demonstrate what’s achievable with careful architecture. 

